            <msContents>
              <summary/>
              <textLang mainLang="syr">Syriac</textLang>
              <msItem n="1" xml:id="a1" defective="true">
                <locus from="1" to="51">Foll. 1-51</locus>
                <author ref="http://syriaca.org/person/13"/>
                <title ref="" type="supplied">Part of the metrical works of Ephraim</title>
                <msItem n="2" xml:id="b1">
                  <locus from="1a" to="2">Foll. 1a-2</locus>
                  <author ref="http://syriaca.org/person/13"/>
                  <title ref="" type="supplied">Admonitory discourse</title>
                  <rubric xml:lang="syr">ܡܐܡܪܐ ܕܡܟܣܢܘܬܐ
                    <locus from="1a"/>
                  </rubric>
                  <incipit xml:lang="syr">ܕܚܠ ܒܪ ܐܢܫܐ ܡܢ ܥܘܼܠܐ. ܕܥܘܼܠܐ ܡܚܪܒ ܐܪ̈ܥܬܐ. ܕܡܒܘܥܐ ܗܘ ܕܒܝ̈ܫܬܐ. <choice><sic>ܕܪܪܐ</sic><corr resp="http://syriaca.org/documentation/editors.xml#wwright">ܕܪܕ̇ܐ</corr></choice> ܘܡܪܘܐ ܣܓ̈ܝܐܐ.<locus from="1a"/>
                  </incipit>
                </msItem>
                <msItem n="3" xml:id="b2" defective="true">
                  <locus from="2b" to="31">Foll. 2b-31</locus>
                  <author ref="http://syriaca.org/person/13"/>
                  <title ref="" type="supplied">The discourses on Faith</title>
                  <rubric xml:lang="syr"><supplied reason="unknown" resp="http://syriaca.org/documentation/editors.xml#wwright">ܡܕܪ̈ܫܐ</supplied> <supplied reason="unknown" resp="http://syriaca.org/documentation/editors.xml#wwright">ܕ</supplied>ܗܝܡܢܘܬܐ . 
                    <locus from="2b"/>
                  </rubric>
                  <finalRubric xml:lang="syr"> ܫܠܡܘ ܡܕܪ̈ܫܐ ܕܗܝܡܢܘܬܐ ܕܡܪܝ ܐܦܪܝܡ ܕܗܘܝܢ ܒܡܢܝܢܐ ܬܡܢܐܝܢ ܘܫܒܥܐ.
                    <locus from="31a"/>
                  </finalRubric>
                  <note>The text presents many variations from that of the Roman edition, sometimes even in the division of the hymns. After fol. <locus from="19">19</locus> there is a leaf missing, comprising from p. 91, A, line 4, to p. 97, F, line 7, of the printed text.</note> <!-- How to indicate what the missing leaf comprises? -->
                  <listBibl>
                    <bibl>Assemani, Bibl. Or., t. i. p. 98, etc.</bibl>
                    <bibl>Ephraemi Opera, t. iii. (vi.), p. 1, etc.</bibl>
                  </listBibl>
                  <msItem n="4" xml:id="c1">
                    <locus from="28b" to="30a">Foll. 28b-30a</locus>
                    <author ref="http://syriaca.org/person/13"/>
                    <title ref="" type="supplied">Small collection of hymns entitled, "Of the Pearl"</title>
                    <rubric xml:lang="syr">ܥܠ ܡܪܓܢܝܬܐ
                      <locus from="28b"/>
                    </rubric>
                    <finalRubric xml:lang="syr">ܫܠܡܘ ܕܥܠ ܡܪܓܢܝܬܐ 
                      <locus from="30a"/>
                    </finalRubric>
                    <note>The small collection of hymns entitled <foreign xml:lang="syr">ܥܠ ܡܪܓܢܝܬܐ</foreign>, "of the Pearl," begins on fol. <locus from="28b">28 b</locus>, but the subscription <foreign xml:lang="syr">ܫܠܡܘ ܕܥܠ ܡܪܓܢܝܬܐ</foreign> is placed at the end of the 5th hymn, fol. <locus from="30a">30 a</locus>.</note>
                  </msItem>
                </msItem>
                <msItem n="5" xml:id="b3" defective="true">
                  <locus from="31a" to="51">Foll. 31a-51</locus>
                  <author ref="http://syriaca.org/person/13"/>
                  <title ref="" type="supplied">The discourses against False Doctrines</title>
                  <rubric xml:lang="syr">ܡܕܪ̈ܫܐ ܕܡܪܝ ܐܦܪܝܡ ܕܠܘܩܒܠ ܝܘ̈ܠܦܢܐ
                    <locus from="31a"/>
                  </rubric>
                  <note>Two leaves are wanting after fol. <locus from="42">42</locus>, comprising from p. 484, A, line 5, to p. 492, D, line 5, of the printed text; and six leaves after fol. <locus from="48">48</locus>, comprising from p. 515, B, line 8, to p. 539, C, line 5. The text terminates, fol. <locus from="50b">50 b</locus>, in the second stanza of the 50th hymn, with the words <foreign xml:lang="syr">ܘܐܠܦ ܕܣܓܝܐ̈ܐ ܡܠܠܘ</foreign> (<bibl>Opera, p. 547, D, line 7</bibl>).</note>
                  <listBibl>
                    <bibl>Assemani, Bibl. Or., t. i. p. 118, etc.</bibl>
                    <bibl>Ephraemi Opera, t. ii. (v.), p. 437, etc.</bibl>
                  </listBibl>
                </msItem>
                <msItem n="6" xml:id="b4">
                  <locus from="51">Foll. 51</locus>
                  <author ref="http://syriaca.org/person/13"/>
                  <title ref="" type="supplied">A small fragment from the collection of hymns entitled "the hymns of Nisibis</title>
                  <rubric xml:lang="syr">ܡܕܪ̈ܫܐ ܕܢܨܝܒܝܢ
                    <locus from="51"/>
                  </rubric>
                  <note>See <ref target="http://syriaca.org/manuscript/305">Add. 14,572</ref>, fol. 114b etc.</note>
                  <listBibl>
                    <bibl>Dr. Bickell's edition, p. 141 etc.</bibl>
                  </listBibl>
                </msItem>
              </msItem>
